- Support provided to RYCO to improve the contractual package of documents with its sub-grantees;
- Applications from CSOs and schools in WB6 region analyzed, selection of grant beneficiaries conducted;
- Contracts with 44 RYCO grant beneficiaries signed and project implementation started;
- RYCO organogram enriched with 11 positions financed by UNDP;
- RYCO M&E framework drafted;
- The design of the methodology and thematic areas of the regional research on young people’s perceptions on peace and security is initiated.

- Strengthen and operationalize RYCOs Small Grants Facility and institutional capacities of RYCO; 
- Consolidate RYCOs Small Grants Facility with additional financial resources (600.000 USD);
- Design RYCOs monitoring and evaluation system and strengthen institutional capacities to conduct M&E;
- implement the regional youth perceptions action research and analyze results;
- Local and regional trainings on leadership, peacebuilding, advocacy and conflict-sensitive research for young activists to empower youth to be actors of change in the region, and to provide structured opportunities for networking across conflict divides;
- National and regional youth consultations to formulate common messages for sustaining peace, enter into dialogue with political parties and decision-makers and create tools, events and products for advocacy and policy and programming impact.

- RYCO staff capacities enhanced in financial grant monitoring, due to formal and on the job traning provided by 7 grant monitoring experts contracted across the WB6 region;
- RYCO subgrantees monitored twice during the scope of their projectsimplementation from the grant monitoring experts.(two spot checks conducted/subgrantee);
