- RYCOs insitutional capacities are enhanced due to development of the Human REsources (HR) Policy, Risk Assessment and Risk Management (RARM) Guidelines, Health Safety and Security in the workplace Policy, Monitoring and Evaluation (M&E) Framework and an IT solution to ease the daily operations and maintain the instutional memory of RYCO office;
- RYCO staff capactities are enhanced as relates the key concepts and the practical use of HR Policy, RARM Guidelines, Safety and Security in the workplace and M&E Framework;
- 24 youth fro WB6 are empowered to be actors of change in the region and to provide structured opportunities for networking across conflict divides, as a result of trainings on leadership, peacebuilding, advocacy and conflict-sensitive research;
- Methodology and syrvey of the regional research on youth peace and security in the WB6 is designed in close cooperation with 24 youth activists and RYCO staff;
- Quantitative data are on the way to be collected in the WB6 region on youth peace and security. quantitative data collection is expected to be finalysed by end of January 2021, followed by qualitative data collection, expected to be finalysed by February-March 2021;

- UNDP finalyses the grant rembursement to RYCO by the end of March 2021;
- Qualitative and quantitative data collection for the regional research on youth peace and security in the WB6 region is finalysed by March 2021 at the latest;
- Data analyses and validation is conducted in cooperation with youth activists. Youth are trained on data analyses;
- Communications and advocacy services are provided to design and content for online platform including photo stories or videos, communications and advocacy strategy and materials, advocacy training for youth;
